  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Water and Sanitation Delivery in Pader &amp; Agago, Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the &#x201C;Sustainable Water and Sanitation Service Delivery&#x201D; program is to provide sustainable access to safe water supply and basic sanitation for formerly displaced people in Acholibur, Pader Kilak, Awere, Pajule, Ogom and Latanye sub counties in Pader district in Uganda. 
The expected results for this project are: 
1. Functional and sustainable service delivery for water and sanitation facilities
2. Improved access to safe water supply 
3. Improved levels of sanitation and hygiene 
4. Efficient community based management and information systems</narrative>
  </description>
